			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmmmmmm..... better idea than the last, but still leaves room for some reservations, perhaps the following questions can be answered.
<br />

<br />
1) What are the average level 20 stats for races with 0 Genius CM going to be like?
<br />

<br />
2) What are the average level 20 stats for races with 7 Genius CM going to be like?
<br />

<br />
3) What are the average level 20 stats for races with 15 Genius CM going to be like?
<br />

<br />
4) How will this help to keep newbies? If not, what is the true rationale behind the set of changes?
<br />

<br />
5) Have they been tested throughly to ensure that there are no unforeseen consequences? (like the over-empowering of certain already powerful races...)
<br />

<br />
6) What bearing has this got on Xeloss/Evintos who are reliant on detection commanders?
<br />

<br />
7) Buckaneers can achieve very high Genius CM, if they get a high detection, coupled with their Famous Privateer ability, what chances are there of outdetecting them?
<br />

<br />
I have a suggestion - how about as a compromise, detection is left out of this loop of changes and growth in detection uses the old formula, since it can be seen that any changes to such stats will only break detection significantly. The other stats can be balanced this way IMO, it'll be fair for high Genius CM races to be able to achieve higher average siege/blockade/siege repelling/break blockade/privateer/raid/maneuver, but detection would definitely break it. Perhaps to answer 1), 2) and 3), try a weighted average out of a random pick of 20 commanders.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.archspace.org/board/images/madkat/narusegawa.gif" border="0" />
<br />
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Leader of Archspace</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
