				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It seems to me that many of these votes did NOT read the last page of this thread. Some people on IRC were reporting really bad commanders with moderate Genius CMs..
<br />

<br />
Make sure you use commanders that have been generated since the changes. Commanders generated before the changes will not have correct starting stats and their starting circumstances will be incorrect. 
<br />

<br />
From the testing I've done so far, I see a great deal of potential from the current changes. Give them a try and offer some realistic and constructive ideas. Obviously there was something missing from the old system or we wouldn't be trying to make improvements. 
<br />

<br />
As for removing detection from the new calculations, I think not. The results I've seen are too promising. If you're not convinced, get on dev, delete all your commanders and start training some from scratch. Dev is currently setup to level your commanders to 20 after one turn of training.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://archspace.org/board/images/madkat/madkat.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
